e non-zero when the dual generator is\nlinear in a subset of the variables.\n  Several groups have studied \"exotic summands\" of the Macaulay dual generator\n$F$. Studying these, we recall a normal form for the Macaulay dual generator of\nan AG algebra that has no \"exotic\" summands. We apply this to Gorenstein\nalgebras that are connected sums.\n  We give throughout many examples and counterexamples, and conclude with some\nopen questions about symmetric decomposition.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 10 Dec 2018 00:52:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 26 Apr 2020 17:26:55 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 19 Jun 2020 22:45:05 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Wed, 29 Jul 2020 16:43:22 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-13"}
